<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="636" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Lawrence</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward.</persName></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Consulate General of the United
                                        States</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Florence</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-03-02"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 2, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> In accordance with the request made by the
                            Secretary of State in circular No. 30, I transmit herewith copies of the
                            royal decrees of King Victor <pb facs="0702" n="1380" xml:id="pg_1380"/>
                            Emanuel of October 29, 1861, and September 11, 1862, establishing for
                            the kingdom of Italy a uniform system of rules and regulations for the
                            collection of external revenue and customs dues.</p>
                        <p>These documents will be found to contain answers to most of the queries
                            propounded by the secretary in the above circular, so far as this
                            kingdom is concerned.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>T. BIGELOW LAWRENCE, <hi rend="italic">Consul
                                General.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Frederick</hi> W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Assistant Secretary of State,
                                    Washington.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>